Weapon List
A weapon's Damage is a fixed number, but its true value lies in its unique properties. The type of weapon you chooseΓÇöbe it a sword, mace, or axeΓÇödetermines how you fight, offering distinct tactical advantages. The material it's made from determines its raw power.
Weapon Properties by Type
Swords (Finesse): Balanced and precise. On a Critical Success (a roll of 1), sword attacks deal an additional +2 damage.
Maces (Bone Breaker): Brutal and heavy. Mace attacks ignore 1 point of the target's Damage Reduction.
War Axes (Hack & Slash): Vicious and sharp. When you hit with a Power Attack, the target also takes 1 Bleed damage at the start of their next turn.
Daggers (Assassin's Blade): Fast and concealable. Dagger attacks deal triple (x3) damage on a successful attack from Sneak (instead of the usual double).

