Curved Blades (one-handed, distinct form factor from Swords)
Governed by the Might Stat. A curved blade is not a reskinned Sword — it is its own weapon type, classified by place of origin and fighting tradition rather than by race/material, since the style travels by trade rather than belonging to one people. No Tier 1 Curved Blade exists; the tradition doesn't produce anything cruder than Tier 2.
Flowing Strike (type property): Once you have spent all your Minor Actions this turn, any attack you make with this weapon triggers one immediate additional attack roll with it on a successful hit. A bonus attack granted this way cannot trigger another. Base damage sits below a straight Sword's tier-equivalent to offset the extra swings this produces over a turn.

