Archery
Governed by the Agility Stat.
Ranged combat is an art form, and the archer's instrument is key to their style. Bows and crossbows are not interchangeable; they offer a fundamental choice between speed, power, range, and tactical flexibility.
Shared Ranged Properties
The following properties can be found on various types of both bows and crossbows, reflecting the specific craftsmanship or intended use of the weapon.
Lightweight: The weapon is designed for stealth. It imposes no penalty on Sneak rolls.
Heavy Draw: The weapon requires significant strength, trading speed for power. It grants +1 Damage but imposes a -1 penalty to your initiative roll.
Long Range: The weapon is exceptionally well-suited for sniping. You have Advantage on attack rolls against targets at the furthest possible range.
Skirmisher: The weapon is maneuverable in close quarters. You do not have Disadvantage when firing at a target in melee range.
Savage: The weapon is crude but vicious. On a Critical Success, the target also takes 2 Bleed damage at the start of their next turn.
Envenomed: The weapon is crafted from toxic materials. You may apply a poison to it as a Free Action instead of a Minor Action.

Bows
Bows are the traditional weapon of the hunter and skirmisher, valuing speed and a continuous stream of arrows over raw power. They are versatile tools for those who need to adapt quickly on the battlefield.
Bow-Exclusive Property
Quick Draw: The weapon is balanced and swift. Using the Eagle Eye perk (spending FP to aim for a bonus) costs 0 FP.

