Crossbows
Crossbows are mechanical weapons of immense power, favored by engineers and dedicated hunters like the Dawngu-ard. They sacrifice speed for armor penetration and staggering force, making every shot count.
Crossbow-Exclusive Properties
Reload: A slow weapon that must be reloaded as a Minor Action after each shot. All crossbows have this property.
Piercing Bolt: The weapon fires with immense force. Its attacks ignore 1 point of the target's Damage Reduction.
Breaching: The ultimate in armor penetration. The weapon ignores 3 points of the target's Damage Reduction.
Bayonet: The crossbow is fitted with a small blade. If an enemy is in melee range, you can use the crossbow to make a melee attack with a Damage of 2.
Weighted: The weapon is heavy and difficult to aim on the move. You have Disadvantage on attack rolls if you moved during the same turn. However, if you do not move, your shots deal +1 damage.

