Social Stigma: Recharging or using an item with a black soul is a dark act. If witnessed by a lawful or good-aligned NPC (a guard, priest, or common citizen), you may be treated with suspicion, reported to the authorities, or even attacked by zealous individuals.
Catastrophe: When you roll a Critical Failure (a 20) while using an item charged with a black soul, you trigger a Soul Catastrophe. The vengeful soul lashes out, and the GM will determine the dire consequences.
