The Art of the Forge: Striking for Perfection
A warrior's skill is paramount, but the quality of their steel can turn a good warrior into a legend. While any smith can shoe a horse or mend a pot, only true artisans can unlock the potential hidden within a blade or a breastplate. This system allows players to invest in their chosen equipment through a high-stakes, high-reward process where a master's touch can forge a common weapon into a priceless artifact. Each swing of the smith's hammer is a gamble, a test of skill against the stubbornness of metal and fate.
The Core Mechanic: Improvement Slots & The Smith's Roll
Every piece of equipment (weapon, armor, or shield) has a set number of Improvement Slots, determined by its material tier. These slots represent the item's inherent potential for reinforcement and refinement.
When a player wishes to upgrade an item, they must pay the required Gold and Material costs. The GM then makes a single d20 roll for the blacksmith, representing their effort in that moment. The outcome determines the quality of the improvement.
Weapons: A successful improvement grants a permanent bonus to the weapon's base Damage.
Armor & Shields: A successful improvement grants a permanent bonus to the item's base Damage Reduction (DR).
